stylometry: When dealing with waiting in lines a manager must consider the possible loss in revenue from people not waiting vs. the cost of changing the line wait time. In general, a long wait time means less people will wait and you would be losing their business. Managers have to look at wether the cost of say adding a new employee to shorten the wait time is worth it , would they bring in enough business to cover the cost of their salary. In the end the objective is for the compnay to make the largest profit possible so if that means adding some to shorten the wait time or missing out on possible customers.
